New Records: Travis Head scored 154 not out, the highest by an Australian in an ODI in England.
Australia's spinners took 9 wickets in total, a new record for the team in ODIs.
Key Match Events: Travis Head's unbeaten century was a major performance.
Marnus Labuschagne contributed with 77 not out and 3 wickets.
Adam Zampa took 3 crucial wickets on his 100th ODI appearance.
Ben Dwarshuis made his ODI debut but was injured early.
Pre-Game Insights: Australia's captain Mitch Marsh won the toss and relied on part-time spinners after key bowlers were unwell.
Travis Head mentioned his relaxed approach and the impact of Jofra Archer's bowling.
England's top order had early struggles but managed a competitive score.
Post-Match Reflections: Mitch Marsh expressed happiness with the win despite initial challenges.
Travis Head was proud of the team's performance and mentioned key moments like the last two wickets.
Marnus Labuschagne was ecstatic with his all-round contributions.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match saw a high-pressure finish with Australia defending 10 runs in the final over.
It was a turning point for Australia after a shaky start.
The spinners' contribution was pivotal to the win.
Others: The match was the first of a series, with the next game scheduled for Leeds.
